description._content: Catalog #: 09_00978 Title: Colonel Cleon Eugene Freeman Special Collection Photo Additional Information: man identified as O. E. Scott in cockpit of Civilian Racer aircraft shaking hands with Frank Dunn. Cleon Freeman was a Captain of the 110th Air Corps Observation Squadron during World War II and served as a liaison officer between the Ninth Air Force and ground forces working in England.
